Introduction cloud computing

What is cloud?
ans: Cloud is the global network of remote server that operates on single ecosystem. These server provides services such as:
i. Storage
ii. Database
iii. Software

What is cloud computing?
ans: Cloud computing is on demand acess to shared computing resources over the internet. It allows you to rapidly scale your resources up or down without needing to buy physcial hardware.

Need of cloud computing 
i. Cost saving(CapEx to OpEx)
ii. Scalability and elasticity
iii. Focus on your bussiness
iv. Data recovery
